				},
				"category": "offensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong> Ran-to has a creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed}</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Ran-to spins the creature he's holding, smashing them against any creatures within his reach, and then throws the creature aside. Ran-to attempts an @Check[athletics|defense:fortitude] check against the grabbed creature's Fortitude DC.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Ran-to tosses his foe a great distance. The grab ends. The grabbed creature is thrown into a space within 30 feet, takes @Damage[14d6[bludgeoning]] damage, and falls @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone}. All creatures adjacent to Ran-to take the same amount of bludgeoning damage (@Check[reflex|dc:34|basic] save).</p><p><strong>Success</strong> As critical success, except the grabbed creatures is thrown into a space within 15 feet, and creatures take @Damage[7d6[bludgeoning]] damage.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> Ran-to tosses his foe aside. The grab ends. The grabbed creature falls prone.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Ran-to loses hold of his foe, causing the grapple to end.</p>",
